**Caregiver Research Study: Your Voice Matters!** <br />
Help us improve support for parents and caregivers of AAC users!


📢 **WHAT IS THIS STUDY ABOUT?** <br />
We're conducting research to understand how caregivers feel about using AAC with their child. Your insights will help improve programs like Club chAT!

👩‍👧‍👦 **WHO CAN PARTICIPATE?**

- Caregivers of children registered for Club chAT at UCP of Greater Cleveland
- Caregivers of children (ages 5-18) using AAC

📝 **WHAT DOES PARTICIPATION INVOLVE?**

- 3 short online surveys (before, after, and 3 months after Club chAT)
- Optional virtual focus group with other caregivers 1 month after Club chAT

💡 **WHY PARTICIPATE?**

- Help improve AAC support for families like yours!
- You will be compensated for your time at all points of participation!

For questions about the study, contact: <br />
Helen Long, PhD, CCC-SLP <br />
Email: helen.long\@case.edu <br />
Phone: 216-368-3484<br />

A collaboration between Case Western Reserve University & United Cerebral Palsy of Greater Cleveland

*Approved CWRU IRB #STUDY20250045*




